=============== Passives ==========
Distress Spores: When the myconid takes damage, all other myconids within 240 ft of it can sense its pain
Sun Sickness: While in sunlight, the myconid has disadvantage on ability checks, attack rolls, and saving throws. The myconid dies if it spends more than 1 hour in direct sunlight
Animating Spores (3/day): As an action, the myconid targets one corpse of a humanoid or a Large or smaller beast within 5 ft of it and releases spores at the corspe. In 24 hourse, the corpse rises as a spore servant. The corpse stays animated for 1d4 + 1 weeks or until destroyed, and it can't be animated again in this way
Rapport Spores: As an action, a 30 ft radius sphere of spores extends from the myconid. Theses spores can go around corners and affect only creatures with an Intelligence of 2 or higher that aren't undead, constructs, or elementals. Affected creatures can communicate telepathically with one another while they are within 30 ft of each other. The effect lasts for 1 hour
